# Statistical Arbitrage Research Framework

## Pairs Trading: An Empirical Study of Mean Reversion Opportunities

---

## Overview

This project develops a statistical arbitrage research framework for identifying and evaluating mean-reversion opportunities between equity pairs.

The objective is to investigate whether statistical relationships between stocks can generate robust trading signals through cointegration-based pairs trading.

The framework includes:

- Pair discovery
- Correlation analysis
- Cointegration testing
- Hedge ratio estimation
- Spread construction
- Z-score signal generation
- Backtesting engine
- Portfolio construction
- Transaction cost analysis
- Interactive Streamlit research dashboard

---

# Research Question

> Can statistical relationships between stocks generate robust trading signals after accounting for risk and transaction costs?

---

# Dataset

The research universe consists of selected large-cap US equities.

Example universe:

- AAPL
- AMD
- BAC
- CVX
- GOOGL
- GS
- INTC
- JPM
- KO
- MA
- MS
- MSFT
- NVDA
- PEP
- SBUX
- V
- XOM

Sample period:


2015 - 2025


