Conclusion

This project demonstrates a complete statistical arbitrage research workflow.

The framework shows that:

Cointegration can identify meaningful relationships between equities.
Mean-reversion strategies can generate trading opportunities.
Portfolio diversification improves risk-adjusted performance.
Transaction costs are a critical factor in real-world deployment.

The project provides a foundation for further development toward a production-level quantitative trading research platform.
